Dear CCA Community,

It is with great sadness that I inform you that Yee Jan Bao, senior adjunct
professor in Painting/Drawing, died on October 16 after a long illness.

Yee Jan was hired at the college in fall 2003 as an adjunct professor and
was promoted to senior adjunct in 2009. He taught in Painting/Drawing and
Diversity Studies through 2011-12.

Yee Jan's exhibition record included shows at PS1, Long Island City, New York;
the New Museum, New York; Stephen Rosenberg Gallery, New York. He received 
grants from the Guggenheim Foundation, the National Endowment for the Arts, 
and the Pollock-Krasner Foundation.

In addition to CCA, he taught at the School of the Art Institute of Chicago,
Rhode Island School of Design, the University of Texas, and the University 
of Chicago.

I first met Yee Jan when we were both teaching in Chicago and we remained 
friends for more than twenty years. On behalf of the college, I extend my
sympathies to his family and wide circle of friends.

Sincerely,
Steve Beal
President
California College of the Arts
